<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE23F6A2ECC4E" blockId="12.[160,1155,280,410]" box="[160,375,280,306]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="B940DB51161AFFF5B59EE23F6A2ECC4E" bold="true" box="[160,375,280,306]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Geographic range</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE21B689DCCE6" blockId="12.[160,1155,280,410]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
A species described originally from 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D3161AFFF5B776E21B6988CC28" box="[584,721,316,340]" name="Madagascar" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, commonly found on islands of East Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2161AFFF5B5CEE2786913CC0B" author="Collingwood CA &amp; Agosti D" box="[240,586,351,375]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref18173" refString="Collingwood CA, Agosti D. 1996. Formicidae (Insecta: Hymenoptera) of Saudi Arabia (part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia. 15: 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti 1996</bibRefCitation>
), and recorded from the Arabian Peninsula from 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D3161AFFF5B59EE2A56BBDCCE6" box="[160,228,386,410]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Oman</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2161AFFF5B5CDE2A56A9ACCE6" author="Collingwood CA" box="[243,451,386,410]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref18149" refString="Collingwood CA. 1985. Hymenoptera: fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia. 7: 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood 1985</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D3161AFFF5B739E2A5690CCCE6" box="[519,597,386,410]" name="Yemen" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2161AFFF5B75AE2A568EECCE6" author="Collingwood CA &amp; Agosti D" box="[612,951,386,410]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref18173" refString="Collingwood CA, Agosti D. 1996. Formicidae (Insecta: Hymenoptera) of Saudi Arabia (part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia. 15: 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti 1996</bibRefCitation>
